1. installing material ui. it is alternative of react-bootstrap
==> npm install @mui/material @emotion/react @emotion/styled
2. use material ui component by {} import component from @mui/material
==> import {Button} from '@mui/material';
==> function App(){
return (
<Button varient="secondary" color="primary"></Button>
);
}
3. varient attribute is used to give background color on component and color attribute is used to give text color on component
==> <Button varient="secondary" color="primary"></Button>
4. sx attribute is used to give incline style on component
==> <Button sx={{color:'red'}}></Button>
